$SPY  *Trading Strategies* #2

Significant Move in Either Direction but Fall More Likely

If you believe the price of an underlying security is volatile think that a significant fall is more likely than a significant rise, then the following strategies are recommended:

Strip Straddle

Key Advantage – Bigger returns than the Long Straddle if the underlying security falls in price.

Key Disadvantage – Potential losses are higher than the Long Straddle.

Strip Strangle

Key Advantage – Upfront costs are lower than the Strip Straddle.

Key Disadvantage – Greater price movement required for a return compared to the Strip Straddle.

Put Ratio Backspread

Key Advantage – No upfront costs required.

Key Disadvantage – Your broker may require you have a high trading level for this strategy.

Via optionstrading.org/

$SPY    *Trading Strategies*

Significant Move in Either Direction but Rise More Likely

The following strategies are good choices when you believe the price of an underlying security is volatile and think that a significant rise is more likely than a significant fall:

Strap Straddle

Key Advantage – Greater profits than the Long Straddle if the underlying security rises in price.

Key Disadvantage – Higher potential losses than the Long Straddle.

Strap Strangle

Key Advantage – Lower upfront costs than the Strap Straddle.

Key Disadvantage – Requires a greater price movement than the Strap Straddle to be profitable.

Call Ratio Backspread

Key Advantage – No upfront costs required.

Key Disadvantages – May need a high trading level with your options broker.

$NETE Net Element Inc. said Wednesday that Mullen Technologies Inc., which it is merging with, has executed a non-binding letter of intent with Unlimited Electrical Contractors Corp. for the purchase of up to 10,000 MX-05 electric vehicles.

UEC is an electrical contractor based in Pompano Beach, Fla., specializing in commercial and residential projects in south Florida, and is trying to be the first electrical contractor with an all-electric service fleet.

Mullen said UEC intends on buying 1,500 MX-05 electric vehicles for its Florida operations, followed up with an additional 8,500 by 2025 for its U.S. West Coast expansion. The initial purchase order is estimated at $75 million.

Net Element shares were up 37% to $15.40 in premarket trading.

So how do we trade this witchy-ness? I usually recommend abstaining from the chaotic market volatility. Imagine faking out all traders in just one day. First, they fake out the bears by gapping up the market, only to crash it to fake out the bulls. Some Quadruple Witching days can do that a few times while others will remain relatively calmer.

Many traders in the java pit will use this day to their advantage by day trading with shorter term targets, while other traders will use it take profits on their longer-term positions, especially if wicked moves are being made. The most important thing is to be prepared for the volatility. 
-TheStockWhisperer.com
